[TABLE from 1. Annual Report 2023-24.pdf, Page 82]
0                                                                                   1
o                 UpStart Commerce Signed on September 12, 2023, this MOU strengthens
     the  collaboration  between  industry  and  academia,  furthering  opportunities
                                                 for students and faculty engagement.
o                  Plus-W This MOU focuses on informing graduates of FAST-NUCES about
                 job opportunities in Japan and supporting their recruitment process.
o         Leverify  Signed \non  September \n20, \n2023, \nthis  MOU \nintroduces \na
                   Management Trainee Officer (MTO) program for FAST-NUCES graduates,
       alongside  placement \nand \ninternship  opportunities \nto \nenhance \ncareer
                                                                           prospects.
o                   Al-Burhan Signed on October 31, 2023, this MOU commits FAST-NUCES
         to  allow  Al-Burhan  to  conduct  workshops  and  sessions  on  Seerah  and
        Tarbiyah  classes,  promoting  character  development  and  spiritual  growth
                                                                      among students.
o               TechVallet Pakistan Signed on April 19, 2024, this MOU provides FAST-
       NUCES  students  across  all  campuses  with  free  access  to  Google  Career
      Certificates, enabling them to gain essential skills in high-demand fields such
                                         as IT, data analysis, and digital marketing.
o             Rapidev Signed on April 2, 2024, this MOU establishes a partnership for
          internships,  placements,  and  mentorship,  providing  FAST  students  and
                              graduates with career guidance and industry experience.
o                Apex Consultants Signed on May 21, 2024, this MOU aims to equip FAST
       graduates with the essential skills required to land jobs in the US job market
                                   through mentorship and career guidance boot camps.
o          Times  Consultants  Signed  on  May  17,  2024,  this  MOU  provides  free
                guidance to FAST-NUCES students pursuing studies abroad, helping them
        navigate \nthe \ncomplexities \nof \ninternational \neducation \nand \ncareer
                                                                       opportunities.
o                AIPS Signed on May 24, 2024, this MOU promotes fully funded training
          programs for faculty and students in the US, including scholarly exchanges,
                                       collaborative research, and lectures/seminars.
o                Agile Conference Pakistan FAST-NUCES hosted the Agile Conferences in
         2023 and 2024, both executed and liaised through the Career Services Office,
  where  industry  professionals  from  across  the  nation  were  trained  on  agile
                                                                       methodologies.
